fferent forms: <i>Mattan(i)ah</i>, <i>Mattatha(h)</i>, <i>Mattithiah</i>, <i>Mattathias</i>, and so on. In the Authorized Version, the evangelist is regularly referred to as <i>Matthew</i>, while the apostle chosen to replace Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":23,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Mathew Snelling was born in 1359, in Derby, Derbyshire, England as the son of John Snellyng. He had at least 1 son with Alice May. He died in 1417, in England, at the age of 58, and was buried in England."},"et":{"1359–1417":"1359–1417","1359–1442":"1359–1442","1401–1455":"1401–1455","1339–Male":"1339–Surnud","1359":"1359","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1382":"1382","1417":"1417","1339":"1339","England":"England","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1359–1417":"1359–1417","1359–1442":"1359–1442","1401–1455":"1401–1455","1339–Male":"1339–Kuollut","1359":"1359","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1382":"1382","1417":"1417","1339":"1339","England":"England","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England"},"fr":{"1359–1417":"1359–1417","1359–1442":"1359–1442","1401–1455":"1401–1455","1339–Male":"1339–Décédé","1359":"1359","1401":"1401","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1382":"1382","1417":"1417","1339":"1339","England":"Angleterre","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, Angle